meta.description: Enables the third-person Model in first-person
meta.long_description:
![](https://trsha.re/1679269573.png)


# First-person Model

Enables the third-person Model in first-person, so you can experience Minecraft from Steve's real perspective. This mod doesn't change any animations, so you also get to see Mojangs "questionable" animation decisions(looking at you, shield + bow). However this mod adds so few and simple mixin hooks into the game, it should work with other mods that come out(MoBends, a real eating/crawling animation, custom 3d armor, etc).

Since this mod is purely visual, it will also work on vanilla servers.

Requires ModMenu(used to change settings).

[![Shockbyte](https://tr7zw.dev/img/shockbyte_black.png?v=2)](https://shockbyte.com//partner/tr7zw)

### Dependencies

- [Not Enough Animations (Forge&Fabric)](https://modrinth.com/mod/not-enough-animations)
- [Fabric API (Fabric)](https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api)
- [ModMenu (Fabric)](https://modrinth.com/mod/modmenu)

### Incompatible

- Epic Fight mod
- Optifine emissive textures
- Sitting on modded chairs/mounts doesn't look right
- FastAnim

### Help, the player head is blocking the camera/add a toggle to hide the player head!

You have an incompatible mod installed. The mod tries everything in its power to hide the head. If it's still visible and blocking the camera, contact the dev of the mod in question. I can't do anything about that.
